T1	Intervention 272 734	The subjects were 112 consecutive patients randomly assigned either to receive MFF (group 1) for 1 week or not to receive MFF, as a control (group 2), after hemorrhoidectomy, The severity of pain and the number of intramuscular analgesic injections required were recorded for the first 3 days, then 1 week after hemorrhoidectomy. The number of days that intramuscular analgesic injections were required, hospital stay, and patient satisfaction were also assessed
